description: A Fair Shake: The Archies are ragging on Betty's tambourine, saying it's not a real instrument! Poor Betty runs into Moose and vents to the big lug. Moose doesn't appreciate it when people hurt his friends' feelings -- so the gang had better apologize, OR ELSE!

The Archies are having a recording session at Veronica's place! But it's a noisy day at the mansion, and things keep interrupting the recording! Can the gang cut a single amongst all the distractions before the tape runs out? Find out in "Constant Replay!"

The Archies are having a recording session at Veronica's place! But it's a noisy day at the mansion, and things keep interrupting the recording! Can the gang cut a single amongst all the distractions before the tape runs out? Find out in "Constant Replay!"

Scribble Dee Dee: Archie has started a petition in school, demanding longer lunch periods. But taking on the establishment can be a scary thing, and not everyone at Riverdale High is brave enough to do it.
The Band Bus: The Archies have a brand new tour bus! Having the name of the band on the side of the bus can lead to a lot of distractions -- or can save them in a jam! Read on and see what we mean!

A Novel Experience: Archie borrowed a library book from Jughead, and now it's almost overdue! Now he has to rush over to Jug's house to give it back before it's too late! But seeing as this is Archie, it probably won't go as planned...
Loser Take All: What do girls see in that bonehead Archie? That's what Reggie asks himself all the time! It's a conundrum that he's out to solve -- once and for all!
Star Gazers: Astrology uses the stars to predict one's future. Sounds crazy, but Archie thinks it's the key to winning over Mr. Lodge! Will he turn out to be right, or will Lodge make him see stars?
Honor Bound: Archie's honor has been offended! What honor, you ask? Good question. He's challenged Reggie to a duel -- again! Will the girls let these goofy gents go through with it?
